<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 02:08:58 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>当人工智能自我构建时</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/when-ai-builds-itself</link><description>如果考虑得足够远，并且有足够的计算能力，这一趋势表明人工智能系统能够完全自主地设计和开发自己的后继系统。这就是所谓的&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/when-ai-builds-itself3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 02:08:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/when-ai-builds-itself</guid></item><item><title>人工智能与微型光学设备相结合，可纠正扭曲的光线，实现更清晰的成像</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ai-paired-with-tiny-optical-device-corrects-distorted-light-for-sharper-imaging</link><description>从显微镜到望远镜再到智能手机相机，镜头缺陷导致的模糊光线在任何地方都是一个问题。加州大学圣地亚哥分校的工程师利用微小但精心设计的光学元件和人工智能，建立了一种从单个图像中发现并纠正这些扭曲的方法，这一步骤可以使先进的光学系统更快、更小、更易于使用。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-paired-with-tiny-optical-device-corrects-distorted-light-for-sharper-imaging.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 01:53:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ai-paired-with-tiny-optical-device-corrects-distorted-light-for-sharper-imaging</guid></item><item><title>蒙克关于基因编辑的辩论</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/munk-debate-on-gene-editing</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 01:38:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/munk-debate-on-gene-editing</guid></item><item><title>大脑回路将记忆与听觉联系起来，揭示了习得的声音如何指导行为</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/brain-circuit-links-memory-to-hearing-revealing-how-learned-sounds-guide-behavior</link><description>短期记忆被认为是在大脑深处的海马体等结构中形成的，但人们对与记忆相关的信息如何以及在大脑中保存在何处以及利用这些信息的过程知之甚少。一个很好的例子是汽车喇叭的声音，我们大多数人都将其视为警告并知道如何做出反应，尽管并非所有喇叭听起来都一样，而且我们每次听到喇叭的情况都不同。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brain-circuit-links-memory-to-hearing-revealing-how-learned-sounds-guide-behavior2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 01:23:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/brain-circuit-links-memory-to-hearing-revealing-how-learned-sounds-guide-behavior</guid></item><item><title>牙齿再生人体试验计划加速推进</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/plans-accelerated-for-human-trials-of-tooth-regeneration</link><description>一家致力于牙齿再生药物的日本生物制药公司刚刚为二期临床试验筹集了数百万美元。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/plans-accelerated-for-human-trials-of-tooth-regeneration.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 01:08:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/plans-accelerated-for-human-trials-of-tooth-regeneration</guid></item><item><title>新黄金标准：当人工智能代币成为未来的货币</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/the-new-gold-standard-when-ai-tokens-become-the-currency-of-the-future</link><description>我花了数年时间观察金融和技术慢慢相互适应，但我们现在正在考虑的转变将在一夜之间改变整个格局。我们需要停止将人工智能仅仅视为一种软件工具或编写电子邮件的酷捷径。我们正式进入一个计算能力成为全球基本商品的时代，而该商品的标准单位就是人工智能代币。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-new-gold-standard-when-ai-tokens-become-the-currency-of-the-future.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 00:53:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/the-new-gold-standard-when-ai-tokens-become-the-currency-of-the-future</guid></item><item><title>谷歌前首席执行官：Eric Sc​​hmidt 和 Dave B 的人工智能实际上会是什么样子</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ex-google-ceo-what-artificial-superintelligence-will-actually-look-like-w-eric-schmidt-dave-b</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 00:38:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ex-google-ceo-what-artificial-superintelligence-will-actually-look-like-w-eric-schmidt-dave-b</guid></item><item><title>大卫·辛克莱博士：如果衰老并非不可避免，但我们实际上可以减缓或逆转它怎么办？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/dr-david-sinclair-what-if-aging-isnt-inevitable-but-we-can-actually-slow-it-down-or-reverse-it</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 00:23:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/dr-david-sinclair-what-if-aging-isnt-inevitable-but-we-can-actually-slow-it-down-or-reverse-it</guid></item><item><title>突破性药物可逆转皮肤衰老并显着加速愈合</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/breakthrough-drug-reverses-aging-in-skin-and-dramatically-speeds-healing</link><description>科学家发现，一种名为 ABT-263 的外用抗衰老药物可以显着改善老年皮肤的伤口愈合。该治疗的原理是去除随着年龄的增长而积累并减缓身体修复过程的受损“衰老”细胞。在老年小鼠中，治疗后伤口愈合得更快，而该药物还激活了与胶原蛋白生成和组织再生相关的基因。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/breakthrough-drug-reverses-aging-in-skin-and-dramatically-speeds-healing.webp" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 00:08:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/breakthrough-drug-reverses-aging-in-skin-and-dramatically-speeds-healing</guid></item><item><title>布朗运动</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/brownian-motion</link><description>是悬浮在介质（液体或气体）中的粒子的随机运动。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brownian-motion.gif" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 23:53:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/brownian-motion</guid></item></channel></rss>